The paper deals with similarity search, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and computer vision (CV). The use of quantization and encoding techniques suggests a focus on machine learning (LG) and databases (DB). Finally, the empirical evaluation of the proposed method on synthetic and real-world datasets suggests a potential fit with multimedia (MM) as well.
